OL,6,FBut once TV-am plunged downmarket and
OL,7,Fsaved itself from disaster, Breakfast
OL,8,FTime started to seem unloved from
OL,9,Fabove.
OL,11,FIt could not compete with its
OL,12,Fdownmarket rival ` nor was it a hard
OL,13,Fnews programme which played to the
OL,14,FBBC's strengths.
OL,16,FYet it was valued, even loved, by its
OL,17,Faudience. Warm and friendly, the
OL,18,Fregular presenters were like extended
OL,19,Ffamily to loyal viewers.
