OL,6,FWhen Breakfast Time was relaunched as a
OL,7,Fnews-driven programme in November 1986,
OL,8,Fthe move was controversial.
OL,10,FIt made strategic sense. A clear choice
OL,11,Ffor morning viewers which also gave the
OL,12,Fprogramme a clearer purpose while the
OL,13,Fnew daytime schedule catered for those
OL,14,Fwho wanted the soft features, cookery,
OL,15,Ffashion and chat.
OL,17,FBut the audience clearly took a while
OL,18,Fto get used to a radically different
OL,19,Fprogramme. The atmosphere was very
OL,20,Fdifferent ` sometimes even sterile `
OL,21,Fand many regular presenters and
OL,22,Fcontributors were dropped.
OL,3,CReflections on the history of BBC
OL,4,Cbreakfast TV
